{"id":24509,"date":"2017-03-10T22:11:02","date_gmt":"2017-03-10T18:11:02","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24509"},"modified":"2024-03-09T12:43:46","modified_gmt":"2024-03-09T08:43:46","slug":"wisdom-abu-dharr","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/03\/10\/wisdom-abu-dharr\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hikmah: The Prophet\u2019s wise advice for Abu Dharr"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Dharr reported: I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, instruct me.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>I advise you to fear Allah Almighty, for it will beautify all of your affairs<\/strong>.\u201d I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>You must recite the Quran and remember Allah Almighty, for you will be mentioned in heaven and you will have light upon the earth<\/strong>.\u201d I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>You must observe long periods of silence, for it will drive away Satan and help you in the matter of your religion<\/strong>.\u201d I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Beware of too much laughter, for it will deaden the heart and take away the light on your face.<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Speak the truth, even if it is bitter.<\/strong>&#8221; I said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Do not fear the blame of any critic in the matter of Allah.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 4592<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><i>Sahih li ghayrihi <\/i><\/strong>(authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0631\u0651\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f